 pod itself needs to start a Ray node that connects to the cluster, then the job script can use the local connection?\n\nI could use a subprocess to start a Ray node with the pod's IP address, getting that from the hostname resolution, and then have the job script connect to the local raylet.\n\nWriting subprocess code...\n\nBut before committing to this approach, I should check if there's a simpler way—maybe the existing Ray setup already exposes a client endpoint I can use directly, or there's something the curl-test pod can already reach.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1471,"cache_read_input_tokens":54067,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1471},"output_tokens":20,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"af75f782-2876-41b6-9bf4-ca19243774ea","uuid":"59f2dfd9-4be3-4464-8ec0-c2b5cd387f5d","request_id":"req_011CcMcG7wzAd8px5rLaayKZ"}
