{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Pjke8meuR2gXJes753H5f8","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The command exits 0 and prints \"pong\". Here's what was done:\n\n**Root cause:** The original script used `ray://ray-head:10001` (Ray Client protocol), but port 10001 is not exposed by the `ray-head` Service — only port 6379 (GCS) and 8265 (dashboard) are.\n\n**Fix:** The updated script now:\n1. Runs `ray start --address=ray-head:6379 --num-cpus=0` to join the Ray cluster as a zero-CPU worker node at the pod's own IP\n2. Calls `ray.init(address=\"ray-head:6379\")` — which works once the local raylet is registered with GCS\n3. Prints \"pong\" and cleans up with `ray stop`\n\nThe ConfigMap `ray-job-script` was patched with the new script, and the pod was recreated so the `subPath`-mounted file at `/opt/job.py` picked up the change."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":753,"cache_read_input_tokens":67529,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":753},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"af75f782-2876-41b6-9bf4-ca19243774ea","uuid":"875d7704-433c-4c7e-864b-b3460d1b7555","request_id":"req_011CcMckwS2d9bKQbo1WHUgo"}
